	<h2>Lesson Plans</h2>
	<hr/>
	<p>Designed as Inquiry Design Model Lessons (IDM), the lessons featured here are centered around a compelling question and three supporting questions. The goal is for students to use the knowledge gained from
engaging in each formative task and answering each supporting question to ultimately create an argument that addresses the compelling question. Ideally, students will also have the opportunity to take informed
action and apply their knowledge to their modern contexts.</p>

	<section class="static-cards-3 my-5">
		<div class="container" style="padding-left: 0px;">
			<div class="row g-4 justify-content-start">
			
			<!-- Card 1 -->
			<div class="col-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
				<%= link_to '/downloads/High%20School%20Post%20WWII%20World%20Order.pdf', target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener', class: "card carousel-card d-block text-reset text-decoration-none shadow-sm h-100" do %>
				<%= image_tag 'carousel/slide1.jpg', class: 'card-img-top', alt: 'Card 1' %>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h4 class="card-title">High School, Post WWII World Order</h4>
					<p class="card-text">Designed as an Inquiry Design Model, this lesson
explores the post-war dynamics between the United
States and the Soviet Union following the Second
World War, focusing specifically on the 1950s. The
sources selected for this lesson were collected with
high-school learners in mind.</p>
				</div>
				<% end %>
			</div>

			<!-- Card 2 -->
			<div class="col-12 col-md-4 col-lg-3">
				<%= link_to '/downloads/Middle%20School%20Civil%20Rights.pdf', target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener', class: "card carousel-card d-block text-reset text-decoration-none shadow-sm h-100" do %>
				<%= image_tag 'carousel/slide2.jpg', class: 'card-img-top', alt: 'Card 2' %>
				<div class="card-body">
					<h3 class="card-title">Middle School, Civil Rights</h3>
					<p class="card-text">Designed as an Inquiry Design Model, this lesson
will help students to understand that the desire to
increase civil rights for Americans has occurred
across American history and is not only tied to the
national fight for rights during the 1950s and 1960s.
The sources selected for this lesson were collected
with middle-grade learners in mind.</p>
				</div>
				<% end %>
			</div>

			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
